<blockquote>

<p>
&nbsp;<p>
<hr size="1" color="#ffffff">
<br>
<p>
</span><span class="Bodytextflush">
<span class="Heading1"><i>The Greater Reality</i></font></span></font>
<p span class="text6">
A greater reality underlies and enfolds the material world that we see, hear, touch, smell, and taste.  Today, we know clearly, certainly the nature of the greater reality and afterlife. People just have to learn what we now know.  Those who come to know will cease to fear death and will live together in peace and brotherhood. When the whole world knows what we know, the whole world will live together in peace and brotherhood.<p>
<p span class="text6">
Our loved ones have never left.  It's just as though they've stepped into the next room for a moment.  There, in the afterlife, they're enjoying a life more wonderful and more real than this life, with youth, vitality, and no pain, sickness, or worry.  There, they wait lovingly, knowing soon we'll step in to join them.
<p span class="text6">
					The Afterlife Research and Education Institute is dedicated to helping people know that we live within a greater reality, that we are spiritual beings having the physical experience portion of our eternal lives, and that humanity can live in harmony and peace if every person knows the fact that there is no death.  Knowing that truth will allow humankind to have great regard, acceptance, and love for all others in all nations with all beliefs.



<p>
&nbsp;<p>
<hr size="1" color="#ffffff">
<br>
<p>
</span><span class="Bodytextflush">
<img src="/images/Death is nothing 419x506.jpg" border="1" bordercolor="#aaaaaa" align="center">


		

<p>&nbsp;<p></span><span class="Bodytextflush">
<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>
<p>
</span><span class="Bodytextflush">
</span><span class="Heading1"><font size="5">
Books Published by Greater Reality Publications

</span>

</b><dir></span>
</span></font><p span class="text6">
					This publishing arm of the Institute supports authors publishing books about the afterlife and afterlife communications. Descriptions of books prepared for publication or published by Greater Reality Publications follow. 
</dir>


<p>&nbsp;<BR>


<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>
<span class="Heading1"><i>Repair & Reattachment Grief Therapy</i></b></font></center></span>
<img src="/images/GAC Cover 150x224.jpg" width="180" height="270" border="0" align="left" hspace="10" vspace="10">
</font></span><p span class="text6">
<i>Repair & Reattachment Grief Therapy</i> is a breakthrough grief therapy procedure that helps clients connect with lived ones in the afterlife. In a single psychotherapy session, 98% of clients will connect, and their grief will be reduced by an average of 86%. This is from the back cover: "People are having their own connections with loved ones in the afterlife, without mediums. The life-changing connections greatly reduce grief and trauma."
<p span class="text6">
The book contains 26 accounts of people who have had their own afterlife connections through the procedure. The accounts are uplifting and inspiring. The loved ones on the next plane of life come to those experiencing the connections to change their lives. 

<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>
<span class="Heading1"><i>Your Eternal Self</i></b></font></center>

<img SRC="/images/YES_180x273" ALT=Your Eternal Self" height=273 width=180 align="left" hspace="10" vspace="10" border="0"></a>
</font></span><p span class="text6">
<i>Your Eternal Self</i> brings together everything we now know about the afterlife, consciousness, the nature of physical reality, and the psychic into a book to help readers know they are eternal beings having a physical experience.  
<br clear="left">

<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>

</span></font></p></center><span class="Heading1"><i>The Fun of Dying!</i></span>
<img src="/images/FOD_180x272.jpg" align="left" hspace="10">
</font></span><p span class="text6">
Now available from Christine F Anderson Publishing & Media.</center>
<p span class="text6">
Roberta Grimes has written a clear description of what happens after a person makes the transition out of the body in <i>The Fun of Dying: Find Out What Really Happens Next!</i>.  

<br clear="left">
<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>

</span></font></p></center><span class="Heading1"><i>The Fun of Staying in Touch!</i></span>
<img src="/images/FOSIT_180x273.jpg" align="left" hspace="10">
<p span class="text6">
Roberta Grimes' second book in the trilogy she is writing about the afterlife, afterlife communication, and spiritual growth describes how people are learning about and maintaining their relationships with people living in the next realm of life.</i> 
<br clear="left">
<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>

</span></font></p></center><span class="Heading1"><i>A Falling Star</i></span>
<img src="/images/Falling_Star180x276.jpg" align="left" hspace="10">
</font></span><p span class="text6">
Olivia had been a vibrant person who enjoyed every minute of her life until she realized she had a dreadful hereditary disease that robbed her of speech and movement. After five years of not being able to communicate with her husband or caregivers, a new person came to her room at the nursing home, and over time, the two women developed a unique connection. Bonnie has the gift of telepathy and eventually, she could understand Olivia’s thoughts. As they became friends and spent more time together, Bonnie helped Olivia express her hopes and fears. This powerful experience took them on an unexpected journey, and along the way, they both found the courage to explore difficult issues and trust in their faith.</i> 

<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>

</span></font></p></center><span class="Heading1"><i>Afterlife Connections: 16 Proven Methods, 86 True Accounts</i></span>
<img src="/images/Afterlife_Connections_180x269.jpg" align="left" hspace="10">
</font></span><p span class="text6">
This anthology of articles written by the presenters at a conference on afterlife communication contains articles by experts in 16 afterlife communications and descriptions of accounts in which people used the methods successfully.</i> 
<br clear="left">
<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>

</span></font></p></center><span class="Heading1"><i>Life in the Afterlife</i></span>
<img src="/images/New_Developments_180x270.jpg" align="left" hspace="10">
</font></span><p span class="text6">
The papers delivered at a conference on new developments in afterlife communication. Authors include Gary E. Schwartz, Ph.D., Rochelle Wright, M.S., R. Craig Hogan,Ph.D., Maria Pe, Esq., Victor Zammit, Ph.D., Sonia Rinaldi, M.S., Mark Ireland, Suzanne Giesemann, M.A., Rosemary Ellen Guiley Bruce Moen, Karen Herrick, Ph.D., Irma Slage, Carol Morgan, Joe Higgins, Anne Puryear, D.D., Herb Puryear, Ph.D., and Susanne Wilson, M.A.</i> 

<hr size="1" color="#770000">
<br>

</span></font></p></center><span class="Heading1"><i>Aspects of Consciousness</i></span>
<img src="/images/Aspects_of_Consciousness_180x272.jpg" align="left" hspace="10">
</font></span><p span class="text6">
The papers delivered at a conference on Aspects of Consciousness in Durham, North Carolina, in 2015.</i> 
